01:26:16.793 --> 01:26:19.328
agreeing that,
yes, there is a problem.


1644
01:26:21.030 --> 01:26:22.698
And then you play.

1645
01:26:22.832 --> 01:26:26.169
You win, and you get
to take that victory lap


1646
01:26:26.302 --> 01:26:28.938
you have been
dreaming about since...


1647
01:26:29.072 --> 01:26:31.374
since you stood
on the sidelines


1648
01:26:31.507 --> 01:26:34.177
watching your big brother
in north Virginia.


1649
01:26:35.711 --> 01:26:39.949
And then change does come
because of you, eventually.


1650
01:26:40.083 --> 01:26:43.119
And that is something
you both can be proud of.


1651
01:26:44.087 --> 01:26:46.756
I got a question.

1652
01:26:46.890 --> 01:26:49.926
Are you completely
fucking heartless,
or just a little bit?


1653
01:26:50.059 --> 01:26:52.561
Oh, my God.
[Emmett] How do you live
with yourself?


1654
01:26:52.695 --> 01:26:56.499
Honestly, how do you live
with yourself?
[shouts] I am not heartless!


1655
01:26:56.632 --> 01:26:58.501
You do not know me!

1656
01:27:00.203 --> 01:27:03.006
You think I don't know
your struggle?


1657
01:27:03.139 --> 01:27:06.810
You think I don't know
what you have come from?
That I haven't been there?


1658
01:27:07.877 --> 01:27:09.578
You think I don't know
what it's like


1659
01:27:09.712 --> 01:27:11.747
to be without heat
in your house?


1660
01:27:11.881 --> 01:27:13.382
That I don't know
what it's like


1661
01:27:13.516 --> 01:27:15.684
to not be able
to afford your jersey,


1662
01:27:15.819 --> 01:27:17.320
and you are
avoiding your coach


1663
01:27:17.453 --> 01:27:20.056
'cause you don't have
the $50 to pay for it?


1664
01:27:21.757 --> 01:27:24.460
[voice breaking]
I ran track at Duke, okay?


1665
01:27:25.895 --> 01:27:27.263
Full ride.

1666
01:27:27.396 --> 01:27:29.332
No big medals, no big wins.

1667
01:27:29.465 --> 01:27:32.802
But I took that money
because it was the only way
I was gonna run myself


1668
01:27:32.936 --> 01:27:35.671
out of that
Red Hook project.


1669
01:27:35.805 --> 01:27:38.407
[scoffs]
You think you know me.


1670
01:27:39.775 --> 01:27:41.644
You don't know me.

1671
01:27:41.777 --> 01:27:45.614
I had to fight and climb

1672
01:27:45.748 --> 01:27:48.084
and crawl to be here

1673
01:27:48.217 --> 01:27:50.219
because I did the work.

1674
01:27:53.556 --> 01:27:58.594
The NCAA spends $3.6 billion

1675
01:27:58.727 --> 01:28:02.298
on student-athlete
scholarships for kids like me,


1676
01:28:02.431 --> 01:28:04.934
like you and like you,

1677
01:28:06.302 --> 01:28:08.504
so that we can get a leg up.

1678
01:28:08.637 --> 01:28:10.573
And what happens
to all of that


1679
01:28:11.640 --> 01:28:13.642
when they start paying you?

1680
01:28:13.776 --> 01:28:15.244
Hmm?

1681
01:28:15.378 --> 01:28:19.615
What happens to volleyball
in Minnesota,


1682
01:28:19.748 --> 01:28:21.650
to soccer in Idaho,

1683
01:28:21.784 --> 01:28:23.953
to softball in South Carolina?

1684
01:28:24.087 --> 01:28:26.455
What happens to
all of those other sports


1685
01:28:26.589 --> 01:28:30.193
that are not men's football
and basketball?


1686
01:28:32.195 --> 01:28:35.731
You out here fighting,
and you forgot
who you're fighting for.


1687
01:28:38.301 --> 01:28:41.370
You know, but...
[clears throat, sighs]


1688
01:28:42.471 --> 01:28:44.173
Hey, what do I know?

1689
01:28:45.341 --> 01:28:46.809
I'm heartless.

1690
01:29:00.256 --> 01:29:01.790
[door opens]

1691
01:29:03.526 --> 01:29:04.994
[door closes]

1692
01:29:08.631 --> 01:29:10.833
[crowd chattering]

