01:30:29.078 --> 01:30:30.946
I would start
with the state prisons.


1720
01:30:31.080 --> 01:30:33.116
Even try
mental health facilities.


1721
01:30:33.249 --> 01:30:35.351
We need to do
a social media backdoor too.


1722
01:30:35.484 --> 01:30:37.286
I doubt that
he even has an account,


1723
01:30:37.420 --> 01:30:39.655
but we have got to find him.
[knocking]


1724
01:30:40.889 --> 01:30:42.658
He is our pressure point.

1725
01:30:42.791 --> 01:30:45.128
Oh. Coach.

1726
01:30:47.596 --> 01:30:49.165
I got your message.

1727
01:30:53.169 --> 01:30:55.471
This thing
we're toying with,


1728
01:30:57.140 --> 01:30:59.442
it's Pandora's box,
you know?


1729
01:31:00.643 --> 01:31:01.810
I know.

1730
01:31:01.944 --> 01:31:03.479
Nobody gets hurt.

1731
01:31:04.713 --> 01:31:06.182
Nobody goes to jail.

1732
01:31:06.315 --> 01:31:09.318
We just play this game.
That's what we all want.


1733
01:31:17.293 --> 01:31:19.462
[coughing]

1734
01:31:19.595 --> 01:31:21.630
[Emmett] Dear Lord,

1735
01:31:21.764 --> 01:31:24.833
the trees are thick,
and we've yet to see a path
through the wilderness.


1736
01:31:26.369 --> 01:31:28.137
Send us a light.

1737
01:31:28.271 --> 01:31:30.473
Show us the way.
Amen.


1738
01:31:30.606 --> 01:31:32.908
Amen. [coughing]

1739
01:31:35.644 --> 01:31:38.847
I can't believe you've
been here this whole time
and didn't tell us.


1740
01:31:38.981 --> 01:31:41.584
What? You thought I was
gonna miss the show?


1741
01:31:41.717 --> 01:31:43.886
[LeMarcus chuckles quietly]

1742
01:31:44.019 --> 01:31:45.421
I'm sorry.

1743
01:31:45.554 --> 01:31:47.690
No, hey, you don't
owe me anything.


1744
01:31:47.823 --> 01:31:50.193
You're the one, the two of you,
who had the guts and vision--


1745
01:31:50.326 --> 01:31:52.528
I meant about her.

1746
01:31:53.629 --> 01:31:55.698
Oh. [inhales sharply]

1747
01:31:55.831 --> 01:31:57.300
Yeah. Her.

1748
01:31:58.301 --> 01:31:59.502
Well...

1749
01:31:59.635 --> 01:32:00.736
[inhales sharply]

1750
01:32:00.869 --> 01:32:02.971
I made my own bed
on that one, so...


1751
01:32:03.106 --> 01:32:05.408
"Thou shalt
not commit adultery"


1752
01:32:05.541 --> 01:32:07.143
is the seventh Commandment.

1753
01:32:10.479 --> 01:32:12.881
Thank you
for clarifying that, Emmett.


1754
01:32:14.016 --> 01:32:15.684
You're welcome.

1755
01:32:15.818 --> 01:32:18.821
[LeMarcus] Look, Elliott,
we can't thank you enough, man.


1756
01:32:18.954 --> 01:32:21.657
Without you, we--
[sighs]


1757
01:32:21.790 --> 01:32:24.193
we wouldn't have even had
a shot to pull this off.


1758
01:32:26.028 --> 01:32:27.730
What's going on here?

1759
01:32:29.265 --> 01:32:31.134
Are we about to hold hands

1760
01:32:31.267 --> 01:32:33.369
and feel good
about your little protest?


1761
01:32:33.502 --> 01:32:36.071
'Cause I thought you guys
were in it to win it.


1762
01:32:36.205 --> 01:32:38.073
You know,
as if it were, say,


1763
01:32:38.207 --> 01:32:40.643
the national title.

1764
01:32:46.215 --> 01:32:49.752
Let me give you a little
something I stumbled across
from my travels.


1765
01:32:51.454 --> 01:32:53.956
I believe that's your coach's.

1766
01:32:55.124 --> 01:32:56.925
Wasn't even wrapped
in aluminum.


1767
01:32:57.059 --> 01:32:59.395
Amateur move.

1768
01:33:01.164 --> 01:33:03.966
Yeah, but what's
the point of this?
We can't unlock it.


1769
01:33:05.368 --> 01:33:08.304
Do you need to?
You know what's on it.


1770
01:33:09.772 --> 01:33:13.041
And you're a quarterback.
You know how to bluff
the other team.


1771
01:33:18.847 --> 01:33:20.383
So you're saying
we keep going?


1772
01:33:20.516 --> 01:33:21.984
[Elliott]
That's not my decision.


1773
01:33:22.117 --> 01:33:24.487
It's not even
about which one is right.


1774
01:33:26.389 --> 01:33:29.057
It's about, which one
are you gonna be able
to live with,


1775
01:33:29.192 --> 01:33:31.260
no matter how it goes,

1776
01:33:31.394 --> 01:33:33.529
how much you suffer
the consequences.


1777
01:33:36.632 --> 01:33:40.303
I'm just letting you know
you still have some options.


1778
01:33:40.436 --> 01:33:43.939
[coughing]
It's off to Rome for me,
comrades.


1779
01:33:44.072 --> 01:33:46.975
Wait, you ain't staying
for the game?
Nah, opiate for the masses.


1780
01:33:47.109 --> 01:33:49.712
It's, like,
too much winning
for my taste.


1781
01:33:53.015 --> 01:33:54.850
I'm so proud
of you guys.


1782
01:33:56.652 --> 01:33:58.321
You did this.

1783
01:33:58.454 --> 01:34:00.689
You alone.
And it was...


1784
01:34:03.091 --> 01:34:05.027
It was
fucking magnificent.


1785
01:34:08.397 --> 01:34:10.165
Veni, vidi...

1786
01:34:10.299 --> 01:34:11.667
Vici.
Vici.


1787
01:34:11.800 --> 01:34:13.602
[door closes]
[coughing]


1788
01:34:14.970 --> 01:34:16.205
[LeMarcus] Goddamn.

1789
01:34:16.339 --> 01:34:17.640
Well...

1790
01:34:19.275 --> 01:34:21.444
we're about due
for our surrender.


1791
01:34:22.578 --> 01:34:24.313
What you thinkin'?

1792
01:34:25.113 --> 01:34:26.682
I don't fucking know.

1793
01:34:27.650 --> 01:34:29.151
My head is pounding.

1794
01:34:29.285 --> 01:34:31.720
Where's that doc?

1795
01:34:31.854 --> 01:34:34.723
Yeah, I'll go get him.
He said he'd wait
in the lobby.


1796
01:34:36.058 --> 01:34:37.226
[coughing]

1797
01:34:37.360 --> 01:34:38.994
Damn, you sick.

1798
01:34:39.127 --> 01:34:42.197
See if I can get you
another IV.
I'll be back in ten.


1799
01:34:46.902 --> 01:34:48.371
[door closes]

1800
01:35:53.302 --> 01:35:56.805
[Mike] As soon as
he gets here, we'll have
the coach and him reunite,


1801
01:35:56.939 --> 01:36:00.643
uh, pleasantries, and then
we'll get right to inviting
the media in.


1802
01:36:00.776 --> 01:36:03.278
I'll give them a few minutes.
They'll go off to play.


1803
01:36:03.412 --> 01:36:05.013
[knocking on door]

1804
01:36:05.147 --> 01:36:06.482
Here we go.

1805
01:36:09.051 --> 01:36:10.218
[Everly] Hey!

1806
01:36:10.353 --> 01:36:12.788
LeMarcus has risen.
There he is.


1807
01:36:12.921 --> 01:36:15.458
All right.
Great to see you.


1808
01:36:15.591 --> 01:36:17.593
Can I get you something?
Some water? A Snickers?


1809
01:36:17.726 --> 01:36:19.595
-[laughter]
-I'm good, thanks.


1810
01:36:19.728 --> 01:36:22.164
[Mike] You were a little
under the weather,
but you're better now.


1811
01:36:22.297 --> 01:36:23.932
Yeah.

1812
01:36:24.066 --> 01:36:26.234
[Mike] That's good news.
[Wes] Not for us.


1813
01:36:26.369 --> 01:36:27.670
[laughter]

1814
01:36:27.803 --> 01:36:29.638
[Everly] True.

1815
01:36:29.772 --> 01:36:31.740
[Mike] Um,
I just wanted to, uh,


1816
01:36:31.874 --> 01:36:34.009
get us to have
a little face-to-face


1817
01:36:34.142 --> 01:36:35.778
before we bring
the cameras in here.


1818
01:36:35.911 --> 01:36:37.780
I was just telling
the coach here


1819
01:36:37.913 --> 01:36:40.282
how impressed I was
with, uh, your conduct.


1820
01:36:40.416 --> 01:36:41.650
Very honorable.

1821
01:36:42.751 --> 01:36:44.119
[Coach Lazor] LeMarcus.

1822
01:36:44.252 --> 01:36:46.021
The team is back.

1823
01:36:47.089 --> 01:36:48.891
They heard
about this deal, and...


1824
01:36:49.858 --> 01:36:51.394
everybody else
is playin' this.


1825
01:36:51.527 --> 01:36:52.995
It's just you
and Emmett now.


1826
01:36:53.128 --> 01:36:56.732
These gentlemen are
giving you a committee,


1827
01:36:56.865 --> 01:36:59.835
and they are gonna address
all of your grievances.


1828
01:37:01.136 --> 01:37:02.471
So,

1829
01:37:03.338 --> 01:37:05.708
time to put on
those pads,


1830
01:37:05.841 --> 01:37:07.643
join your brothers,
and do battle.


1831
01:37:08.644 --> 01:37:10.212
Everybody's countin'
on you.


1832
01:37:11.947 --> 01:37:13.882
I'm countin' on you.

1833
01:37:17.319 --> 01:37:19.187
You know, I assure you,
LeMarcus,


1834
01:37:19.321 --> 01:37:21.123
this isn't
a ceremonial committee.


1835
01:37:21.256 --> 01:37:23.358
We're gonna dig down
into these issues


1836
01:37:23.492 --> 01:37:26.395
and figure out
what's best for all of us.


1837
01:37:29.264 --> 01:37:30.866
All right?

1838
01:37:30.999 --> 01:37:33.068
Like the coach said,
we have a game to play.


1839
01:37:33.201 --> 01:37:35.203
Let's get the cameras in...
I didn't say yes.


1840
01:37:36.539 --> 01:37:38.240
[Everly]
What's that?


1841
01:37:39.174 --> 01:37:40.509
I didn't say yes.

1842
01:37:42.845 --> 01:37:44.680
[sighs]

1843
01:37:47.182 --> 01:37:49.084
What would it take
in your mind


1844
01:37:49.985 --> 01:37:51.920
to get to yes?

1845
01:37:54.089 --> 01:37:56.224
Well, our demands
haven't changed.


1846
01:38:00.763 --> 01:38:02.731
[chuckles]

1847
01:38:31.727 --> 01:38:33.629
[Katherine] That's
the sealed case file


1848
01:38:33.762 --> 01:38:36.064
from that fateful night
at the Gin Mill.


1849
01:38:38.834 --> 01:38:42.605
The detectives investigated
for two weeks, and then...


1850
01:38:42.738 --> 01:38:44.172
[sighs]

1851
01:38:44.306 --> 01:38:48.777
...suddenly, K.C. Walton
decided to drop the charges.


1852
01:38:55.117 --> 01:38:58.020
A lot of movin' pieces
in there, LeMarcus.


1853
01:38:58.987 --> 01:39:00.823
This thing is a minefield.

1854
01:39:02.625 --> 01:39:04.927
You find my brother yet?
[Katherine]
Getting close.


1855
01:39:05.060 --> 01:39:09.164
I'd really love
to stop the search
and just have a beer,


1856
01:39:10.298 --> 01:39:12.034
watch a football game.

1857
01:39:15.638 --> 01:39:17.773
Well, why don't
we tell 'em, Coach?


1858
01:39:19.107 --> 01:39:20.643
We're a wolf pack, right?

1859
01:39:22.611 --> 01:39:24.513
We hunt together,
we starve alone.


1860
01:39:24.647 --> 01:39:26.414
Ain't that the creed
you always preach?


1861
01:39:26.549 --> 01:39:29.985
Why don't we tell everybody
how high up this really goes?


1862
01:39:30.118 --> 01:39:32.020
Stop. Just stop.

1863
01:39:32.154 --> 01:39:35.090
Look, you come out
of this now,


1864
01:39:35.223 --> 01:39:37.459
you're not just
a Heisman Trophy winner,


1865
01:39:37.593 --> 01:39:39.528
NFL first-rounder.

1866
01:39:41.096 --> 01:39:44.332
You're an icon now.
You've already
accomplished that.


1867
01:39:44.466 --> 01:39:47.469
You're the Curt Flood
of collegiate athletics.


1868
01:39:48.637 --> 01:39:50.806
You're making
history here already.


1869
01:39:50.939 --> 01:39:52.641
They're gonna write books
about you.


1870
01:39:52.775 --> 01:39:55.077
Now, don't throw
everything away for-for


1871
01:39:55.210 --> 01:39:57.713
whatever this
self-righteous bullshit is.


1872
01:39:57.846 --> 01:39:59.481
Come on, man.
You've worked too hard.


1873
01:39:59.615 --> 01:40:00.849
[grunts softly]

1874
01:40:00.983 --> 01:40:03.318
We've worked too hard
for this.


1875
01:40:04.352 --> 01:40:06.521
Let's just go
fuckin' win this thing.


1876
01:40:08.190 --> 01:40:09.658
[scoffs]

1877
01:40:09.792 --> 01:40:10.826
Win.

1878
01:40:12.695 --> 01:40:14.930
That's all that
really matters, right?


1879
01:40:16.665 --> 01:40:18.133
Just win.

1880
01:40:19.702 --> 01:40:21.637
So that's what I did.

